<span class="displaytext"><b> <u>strengthening our economy by lowering the tax burden on seniors:</u> </b> <p><b>today, governor (candidate full) discussed his strategy to strengthen our economy by reducing the tax burden on seniors.</b> our economy is facing unprecedented challenges and seniors face many of the same burdens of a slowing economy as families nationwide. governor (candidate last) has proposed an economic stimulus package that will help all seniors as they work and save. </p><p><b> <u>eliminating payroll taxes on working seniors:</u> </b> </p><p><b>to help working seniors, governor (candidate last) will permanently eliminate payroll taxes on employees over the age of 65.</b> it is not fair that seniors that have worked their whole life and earned their full social security benefit continue to owe payroll taxes to the federal government. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- in this uncertain economic environment, more and more seniors are returning to the workforce.</b> from 2003 to 2006, the ranks of working seniors increased by 754,000. governor (candidate last)'s proposal will provide an immediate tax cut to working seniors. </p><p><b>- governor (candidate last) believes that seniors have already earned their full social security benefit and should not owe additional payroll taxes for income earned after age 65.</b> </p><p><b>- governor (candidate last)'s plan to eliminate payroll taxes for working seniors will help more than 5.3 million working seniors nationwide.</b> almost 400,000 working seniors in florida will benefit from governor (candidate last)'s bold proposal. the level of employment in florida for workers over 65 jumped from 302,000 to 381,000 between 2003 and 2006. this is an increase of 79,000 workers â€“ a 26.2% jump. </p></blockquote> <p><b> <u>lowering the tax burden on seniors and the middle class: <br/></u> </b> <br/> <b>to help all americans, governor (candidate last) will make middle-class savings tax free.